---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'How to Drink Baijiu Without Wasting It';
const description = 'Learn how to serve, smell, sip, toast, and pair baijiu so the drink makes sense instead of feeling like a harsh challenge.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <header class="article-header"><div class="narrow"><p class="eyebrow">Serving Guide</p><h1>How to Drink Baijiu</h1><p class="lede">Baijiu is often served in tiny cups, but that does not mean the only way to drink it is to throw it back without tasting.</p></div></header>
  <section class="content"><article>
    <h2>Use Small Pours</h2><p>Small cups help manage intensity. Smell first, take a small sip, and let the aroma unfold with food.</p>
    <h2>Pair With Food</h2><p>Baijiu often works better with meals than alone. Rich meat, spicy dishes, grilled foods, pickles, and savory sauces can make strong aromas feel more integrated.</p>
    <h2>Understand Toasting</h2><p>In banquet settings, baijiu can carry social meaning. You do not need to imitate every drinking rhythm blindly. Pace, politeness, and clarity matter.</p>
    <h2>Try Cocktails Carefully</h2><p>Rice aroma and some light/strong aroma bottles can work in cocktails, but intense sauce aroma can dominate a drink. Use it like a powerful flavor ingredient.</p>
  </article></section>
</BaseLayout>
